<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10053f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10053f">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10053f"> 53(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Indian traintops white</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Un tr&egrave;s curieux mod&egrave;le de bureau ambulant est celui qui est en usage sur les r&eacute;seaux de l&apos;Inde britannique, <i>Indian Railway C<sup>o</sup></i>, et qui se distingue par un syst&egrave;me de plafonds. Entre le plafond et la couverture ext&eacute;rieure, on a m&eacute;nag&eacute; un espace. <mark>La couverture ext&eacute;rieure est peinte en blanc</mark> pour renvoyer les rayons du soleil; <font color="green">[A very curious model for the ambulatory office is the one used on the British Indian rail network, the Indian Railway Co., which had a unique system of roofs. Space is arranged between the roof and the exterior covering which is painted white to reflect the sun&apos;s rays]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 146-7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
